@baseUrl = http://localhost:5003

### Auth endpoints
### Login to get JWT token
# @name login
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "username": "admin",
    "password": "admin123"
}

### Store the token from login response
@authToken = {{login.response.body.token}}

### 1. Test WeatherForecast (No Auth Required)
GET {{baseUrl}}/WeatherForecast

### 2. Get All Employees (Protected - Requires Admin Role)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/Employees
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### 3. Create New Employee
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/Employees
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "firstName": "John",
    "lastName": "Doe",
    "email": "john.doe@example.com",
    "department": "IT",
    "position": "Developer",
    "salary": 75000,
    "dateOfJoining": "2023-10-19",
    "phoneNumber": "1234567890",
    "status": "Active"
}

### 4. Get Employee by ID (after creating, replace {id} with the actual ID)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/Employees/1

### 5. Update Employee (replace {id} with actual ID)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/Employees/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "id": 1,
    "firstName": "John",
    "lastName": "Doe",
    "email": "john.updated@example.com",
    "department": "IT",
    "position": "Senior Developer",
    "salary": 85000,
    "dateOfJoining": "2023-10-19",
    "phoneNumber": "1234567890",
    "status": "Active"
}

### 6. Delete Employee (replace {id} with actual ID)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/Employees/1

